{
  "_README": [
    "Hand-maintained signature annotations for the generated Lua API inventory.",
    "Util/update_docs.py extracts the SYMBOL inventory (table/function/type/method",
    "names and receivers) mechanically from the binding sources; the C++ macros do",
    "NOT carry Lua argument names or return types, so those live HERE. Editing this",
    "file is how a signature stays accurate WITHOUT hand-editing the generated doc",
    "text: the generator reads these entries and rewrites the marked blocks.",
    "",
    "Keys are the canonical symbol id the generator computes:",
    "  table function      world.get           (dot)",
    "  global function     loc                 (bare name)",
    "  type constructor    Vector3             (the type name)",
    "  instance method     Vector3:length      (colon)",
    "  static/singleton    InputActions.getSingleton   (dot)",
    "  member field        Vector3.x           (dot)",
    "Each entry: { \"sig\": \"(args) -> ret\", \"doc\": \"terse purpose\" }.",
    "'sig' omits the receiver and, for a constructor, is just the argument list.",
    "A symbol found in the sources but absent here renders with a '(...)'",
    "placeholder and is reported by --check; an entry with no matching symbol is",
    "reported as stale. Neither is fatal - both are drift signals to act on."
  ],
